abstract: With more than 15,000 people killed by gun violence in the United States last year - not counting suicides - Democrats running for their party's presidential nomination are pointing to inaction in Washington as evidence they should be chosen to run against Republican President Donald Trump.
snippet: With more than 15,000 people killed by gun violence in the United States last year - not counting suicides - Democrats running for their party's presidential nomination are pointing to inaction in Washington as evidence they should be chosen to ru...
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - With more than 15,000 people killed by gun violence in the United States last year - not counting suicides - Democrats running for their party's presidential nomination are pointing to inaction in Washington as evidence they should be chosen to run against Republican President Donald Trump.
headline_main: Background Checks and Bump Stock Bans: 2020 Democrats on Gun Control
headline_print_headline: Background Checks and Bump Stock Bans: 2020 Democrats on Gun Control

abstract: Readers analyze the defense arguments and the debate over witnesses. One muses how senators might vote differently if it were a secret ballot.

abstract: President Donald Trump on Wednesday signed a new North American trade agreement during an outdoor ceremony at the White House attended by about 400 guests - but not the key Democrats who helped secure congressional passage of the deal.
